A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Long Range Stand-Off (LRSO) effort will develop a weapon system to replace the Air Force's Air Launched Cruise Missile (ALCM), operational since 1986. The
LRSO weapon system will be capable of penetrating and surviving advanced Integrated Air Defense Systems (IADS) from significant stand-off range to prosecute
strategic targets in support of the Air Force's global attack capability and strategic deterrence core function.

This program element included all necessary expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver weapon system capability. The use of such program funds would be in
addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in program elements 0605829F, 0605831F, 0605833F, and 0605898F.

This program is conducting Engineering and Manufacturing Development tasks to validate requirements to support Developmental and Operational Testing, and
Production Readiness.

Pre-planned Product Improvement (P3I) efforts are necessary to keep LRSO ahead of emerging adversary technologies and are separate from the LRSO Program of
Record. Adversary investments in Integrated Air Defense Systems (IADS) and additional territorial gains necessitate these efforts to maintain LRSO's effectiveness
beyond the reference used to validate LRSO requirements (30-year service life). Budget year 2027 through the FYDP investments are imperative to key focus areas for
P3I efforts based on intel rationale to enhance future survivability.

This program is in Budget Activity 5, System Development and Demonstration (SDD) because it has passed Milestone B approval and is conducting engineering and
manufacturing development tasks aimed at meeting validated requirements prior to full rate production.




