       Change Summary Explanation
       The FY 2026 President's Budget submittal did not reflect the FY 2027 through FY 2030 funding. Therefore, an explanation of the changes between the two
       budget positions for FY 2027 cannot be made in a relevant manner.

       FY2026 to FY 2027 net increase of $689.131 million due to:
       $519.768 million for Long Range Kill Chain test capability development; $150.899 million for hypersonic test capabilities; $24.405 million to restore bomber
       flight test; 18.333 million for inflation, fuel pricing, and supply rate changes; $15.858 million for test facilities operations transfers; $12.253 million for F-35
       developmental test; $11.548 million for Department of War Enhanced Performance Awards; $5.429 million for Joint Simulated Environment testing; $3.114
       million for VENOM aircraft operations; $1.5 million for major investments; -$11.518 million programmed decrease to developmental test aircraft; -$14.5 million for
       removal of FY 2026 BA136 adds; and -$47.958 million net reduction for baseline adjustments, retirement system contributions, civilian pay adjustments, internal
       adjustments, and government efficiencies.

       FY 2026 (Current Year) was reduced by $40.634 million, and FY 2027 Budget Year was reduced by $44.511 million for civilian personnel to optimize the
       workforce in compliance with Executive Order 14210, "Implementing the President's Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative.”




