will address current and future training requirements and implement new functionality to support more complex
training requirements related to Underwater, Surface and other warfighter upgrades.

FY 2025 Plans:
- Continue development, integration and testing of ATD on AEGIS with new capabilities being implemented into
CP 24-1/BL 10.X and enable leveraging for Ship Self Defense System (SSDS) BL 12.X including Cooperative
Engagement Capability (CEC).
- Continue to design, develop, and test of Advanced Training Domain (ATD) modifications aligned to the
Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS) and ICS to deliver LVC training with Combat System Simulation/Stimulation
(CS3) in-stride with Combat System deliveries from the SW Factory.
FY 2026 Base Plans:
- Continue development, integration and testing of ATD on AEGIS with new capabilities being implemented into
CP 24-1/BL 10.X and enable leveraging for Ship Self Defense System (SSDS) BL 12.X including Cooperative
Engagement Capability (CEC), staying current with evolving combat system builds.
- Continue to design, develop, and test of Advanced Training Domain (ATD) modifications aligned to the
Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS) and ICS to deliver LVC training with Combat System Simulation/Stimulation
(CS3) in-stride with Combat System deliveries from the SW Factory.
