Note
Starting in FY26, Project 1447 will be consolidated in 4 major efforts:
1. AEGIS Development Support: Common Services required to support Baseline Development and Testing
2. BL 5/7 Destroyer Upgrades: focused on providing warfighting improvements to ships fielding with BL 5 and 7.
3. BL 9 Destroyer Continuous Warfighting Improvements: focused on providing ongoing warfighting improvements to ships fielded with Baseline 9 and SPY-1
configuration to ensure these ships continue to pace the Threat.
4. BL 10 Destroyer Continuous Warfighting Improvements: focused on providing ongoing warfighting improvements to ships fielded with Baseline 10 and SPY-6
configurations to ensure these ships continue to pace the Threat.

A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
AEGIS Development Support is the foundation that maintains the Research and Development Land Based Test Facilities, Technical Design Agent (TDA), Commercial
Off The Shelf (COTS) hardware engineering, and Program Management services required to support the development and integration efforts required to effectively
design, test and certify, Combat System computer programs. Starting in FY26, this line will support the Combat System Test Bed (CSTB) efforts, which support model
development designed to reduce testing requirements.

AEGIS BL 9.2.2 delivered in FY21 to TI-12 hardware ships, integrated previous CSL capabilities plus Surface Electronic Warfare Improvement Program (SEWIP)
BLK 2 integration (auto association); MH-60R integration; Advanced Training Doman; Boundary Defense Capability; Integrated Air and Missile Defense (IAMD)
mission planner; Above Water Sensor Coordinator; Agile Moondog, Sirocco, Sundog part 1, Silent Squall part 1, and Vortex; Advanced Calibration Experiment; Cyber
enhancements (cyber resource services, boundary proxy service, Security Information and Event Management (SIEM), network device integrity, update manager); and
BMD 5.1.3.1 (MDA-developed). BL 9.2.2 delivered the previously listed capabilities plus warfighting improvements derived from operations in the Red Sea to remaining
TI-12H ships in FY24. BL 9.2.2 will deliver previously listed capabilities with further threat-based modernization improvements derived from Red Sea operations to
TI-12H ships in FY25. (Effort Completes in FY25)

AEGIS Capability Package (CP) 2022, delivered in FY23, builds upon previous CSL capabilities, integrating Multi Mission Signal Processor (MMSP)-Restoration
(AMOD DDG only); AEGIS Linear Processing System (ALPS); High-Energy Laser with Integrated Optical-Dazzler and Surveillance (HELIOS); SM-2 Blk IIIC initial
capability; Agile Firestorm; Mk 38 Mod 4 Engineering Operational Sequencing System (EOSS) integration; and BMD 5.1.4 (MDA-developed) capabilities. CP 2022-2
delivered to DDG 91 to support its modernization test program in FY24. Dependent on SEWIP BLK 3 Integration effort. CP 2022-2 was delivered to DDG 91 to support
its modernization test program in FY24. Dependent on SEWIP BLK 3 Integration effort. (Effort Completed in FY24) Previously listed capabilities with Infrastructure as


