AEGIS Capability Package (CP) 2024 delivers previous CSL capabilities, integrating additional warfighting improvements to include Evolved Sea Sparrow Missile
(ESSM) BLK 2 Optimized, Elevated Radar Advanced Experiment (ERACE) integration, SEWIP BLK 3 Test Certification, Cooperative Engagement Capability (CEC)
BLK II Integration Capability Group 3 (CIG 3), Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS), urgent fleet needs, and BMD 5.1.5 with SBT Inc 3 (MDA-developed). IaaS integration
virtualizes the AEGIS Weapons System and enables the rapid testing and delivery of new warfighting capabilities to ships. (Effort Completes in FY25)

SEWIP BLK 3 Integration brings non-kinetic electronic attack capability into the AEGIS Weapons Systems inventory, expanding the number of threats the AEGIS Fleet
can counter. (Effort Completed in FY24)

Baseline 5/7 Destroyer Upgrades will provide updates to legacy configurations to address emergent requirements impacting the operational performance of the combat
system and address cyber challenges. Current plan is focused on AEGIS BL 5.4.1 delivering NGSSR integration; Global Positioning System (GPS), Navigation, and
Timing Service (GPNT)S; portions of Agile Sundog, Silent Squall, & Vortex; Command and Control Processor (C2P) tech refresh; and BMD 4.1.3 (MDA-developed).
Supports installations beginning in FY25. Supports future updates to address critical upgrades required to maintain effectiveness of the AEGIS Combat System for both
AEGIS BL 5 and 7 configurations.

Baseline 9 Destroyer Continuous Warfighting Improvements (Previously Aegis Capability Package 2026) delivers previous CSL capabilities plus additional warfighting
improvements necessary to improve operational effectiveness and address future threats. Specific warfighting improvements were defined in FY24 and will deliver to
ships beginning in FY26 and support annual deliveries to support continuous development, continuous integration, and continuous delivery to ensure AEGIS DDG's
maintain and evolve to address advanced threats.

Baseline 10 Destroyer Continuous Warfighting Improvements delivers previous CSL capabilities plus additional warfighting improvements necessary to improve
operational effectiveness and address future threats. Currently this effort is focused on the following efforts:
1. AEGIS BL 10.0 provides critical warfighter improvements on AEGIS FLT III DDGs, delivering in FY24. AEGIS BL 10.0 combat system development efforts include
integration of the Air and Missile Defense Radar (AMDR) SPY-6(V)1 radar while building upon AEGIS BL 9 to form the AEGIS FLT III DDG Combat System. BL 10.0
delivers previous BL 9 Common Source Library (CSL) capabilities plus SPY-6(V)1; Mk 160 Gun Combat System (GCS) concurrent engagements; Close in Weapon
System (CIWS) sensor integration; Tactical Data Link (TDL); and the Missile Defense Agency's Ballistic Missile Defense 6.0 (BMD 6.0) program (MDA-developed).
Fields to new construction FLT III DDGs beginning FY24 in support of the Air and Missile Defense Commander (AMDC) fleet requirement.
2. AEGIS BL 10.0.1 continues combat system development efforts to include integration of the Technical Insertion (TI) 16 Mod 1 hardware suite, Red Hat Enterprise
Linux (RHEL) 8.0 operating environment, Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS), and combat system element updates. Fields to new construction FLT III DDGs beginning in
FY25 in support of the AMDC fleet requirement and BMD Flight Test Missions.
3. AEGIS BL 10.1 includes Sea Based Terminal Increment 3, enhancing hypersonic defense capability, optimization of AN/SPY-6(V)1 radar detection and engagement
performance, as well as expansion of Electronic Attack/Electronic Protection measures. Anti Air Warfare capability will have improved performance against deceptive



