The SUBNET program will build upon previous successes by championing R&D projects focused on creating a more resilient,
intelligent, and sustainable subsistence supply chain for the Warfighter. The plan will pivot towards next-generation solutions that
ensure operational dominance in contested environments and enhance/ensure food safety, quality, and security. Key initiatives
will include the development of advanced data analytics and logistics technologies to improve demand forecasting and optimize
resupply operations in anti-access/area denial (A2/AD) environments, directly addressing future "push logistics" and continuity
of operations (COOP) requirements. The program will also explore research into innovations in Class I sustainment, exploring
novel food production/processing methods and ration components designed to meet the unique Warfighter mission requirements.
