D. Acquisition Strategy
SBIR is a three-phase program that provides early-stage R&D to small companies. Eligible projects must fulfill an R&D need identified by the Department of Defense and
have the potential to be developed into a product or service for commercial or defense markets. SBIR is designed to stimulate technological innovation, increase private
sector commercialization of federal R&D, increase small business participation in federally funded R&D, and foster participation by minority and disadvantaged firms in
technological innovation.




