Description: This program provides rapid and focused acquisition for state-of-the art forensic Identity Operation
capabilities as a mission enabler for the five operational pillars of Irregular Warfare and supports Find, Fix,
Finish, Exploit, Analyze and Disseminate (F3EAD) cycle. Exploitation Analysis Capability (EAC) is a modular and
scalable SO-peculiar (SO-p) forensic laboratory environment utilized for more in-depth exploitation of captured
exploitable material (CEM). Biometrics enable the collection and transmission of unique and measurable
human signatures that are then used to verify against or enroll into the DoD authoritative databases. Document
and Media Exploitation (DOMEX) is a scalable, modular, and adaptable multi-disciplined capability that
provides the means to identify, exploit, translate and produce reports on documents and electronic media of
immediate tactical value. Forensic exploitation is a scalable, modular and adaptable multi-disciplined forensic
science capability to recover, identify, and conduct analysis of chemistry based Collectible Exploitable Material
(CEM). Supports the 2025 Interim National Defense Strategy; CEM sharing with foreign partners and provides
intelligence to advance regional security goals that implement the higher-level aims of integrated deterrence.

FY 2025 Plans:
Continue development, test and evaluation of advanced DOMEX capabilities to conduct non-destructive
exploitation of small Uncrewed Multi-Domain Systems (sUMS) and enhanced forensic chemistry capabilities for
point of origin identification of compounds.
FY 2026 Base Plans:
Continues development, test, and evaluation of Biometric Devices (Identification and enrollment kit), along with
rapid innovative prototyping and enhanced forensic chemistry capabilities for point of origin identification of
compounds.
FY 2025 to FY 2026 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Increase of $0.027 million supports rapid innovative prototyping, engineering support and testing efforts.
